==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dichogamy
<hw>Di*chog"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ in two,
asunder + <?/ marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The condition of
certain species of plants, in which the stamens and pistil do not mature
simultaneously, so that these plants can never fertilize
themselves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dichotomist</ent>⟦br⟧
